@NODE Requirements "Requirements"

- ARexx

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"

Copy AppLauncher.rexx to REXX:.

Copy AppLauncher.cfg to S: or change the variable »configname« in the
script.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "Usage"

@{b}Arguments@{ub}

AppLauncher.rexx APPNAME [TOFRONT] FILES

APPNAME The name of the application as defined in the config file
TOFRONT Brings application to front
FILES   Guess what! The names of the files to load.

Beware: Not all applications support loading of more than one file.


@{b}Example@{ub}

AppLauncher.rexx Photogenics TOFRONT bild1.jpg bild2.jpg
AppLauncher.rexx TurboCalc Test.TCD


@{b}Config file@{ub}

[Photogenics]                               name of application
    Portname = PHOTOGENICS.1                name of arexx port
    ToFrontCmd = PGSTOFRONT                 command to bring it
                                            to the front
    LoadCmd = LOAD                          command to load a file
    Filename = Photogenics                  filename of application
    Pathname = PRG:Grafik/Photogenics       pathname of application
    Stack = 25000                           stack (look in the icon!)

In the provided config file are some settings for some application. You
normally only need to adapt the path names.

If you add new settings to the config file, please send a copy of them to
me so that I can include them in the next release. Thanks in advance.


@{b}Use in DOpus 5.x@{ub}

Use {f} for the first selected file or {F} for all selected files as files
argument. Note: Some applications do not support more than one file at a
time.

